Epilogue:<br>
<br>
It is late in the afternoon and the King has left the Hidden-Tower for the second time, this time with the Queen and his most faithful Wizard in tow. The locks have been changed so that they will only answer to the King and Queen and their Heirs.<br>
<br>
The King and Queen have issued a proclamation that has gone forth through-out the Faydarks.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hear Ye, Hear Ye, let it me known through-out the Land.<br>
Elections will be held for offices of the Star Council.<br>
The winners, chosen by all the peoples of the Eldritch shall<br>
Bear the title of Duke or Duchess.<br>
<br>
The elections shall be held as follows:<br>
<br>
All Casters shall gather together and vote into offices of Marquis and Marquisses those they wish to lead in the guilds of Enchanters, Wizards, and Mages; and a Duke or Duchess of High Tower to represent them all in the Royal Court.<br>
<br>
All of the Priest classes shall gather together and vote into offices the Marquis and Marquisses to lead the guilds of Clerics, Druids, and their protectors, the Paladins; and a Duke or Duchess of the Papacy to represent them all in Royal Court.<br>
<br>
All of the trade and land Barons shall gather together and vote into offices three Marquis and/or Marquisses to lead them; and a Duke or Duchess of the Mithrals to represent them all in Royal Court.<br>
<br>
All of those who protect the realm shall gather together and vote into offices the Marquis and Marquisses to lead the guilds of Warrior Fier'Dal, Warrior Koada'Dal, Rangers, and Scouts; and a Duke or Duchess of the Guardians to represent them all in Court.<br>
<br>
These four Dukes and Duchesses shall serve as the Star Council representing the people as a parliament before the King and Queen in Royal Court. A fifth member of the Star Council, the Peacekeeper, has been chosen by the King and Queen and will serve to keep peace among the council and vote as tie-breakers should the need arise. &quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
At present count, Ascrida Ramaloke of the Order of the Elder Dragons leads in the race for Marquisse Enchantress, as does Garchoo of the Fellows of Valor leads in the race for Marquis Wizard. Cresida Peregryn leads for the Clerics, Aegaras Ashenblade ties with Rhoenil Brindleheart for the Druids, and Hawkeblade Steelheart, also of the Fellowship of Valor runs for the Paladins. The Marquis and Marquisse of the Mithrals are still being argued, but it appears the Duke of Mithrals may very well be given to Arbyr Naurgalad of Solus. Among the Guardians, both wood-elf and high-elf warrior guilds still argue, but Legadas Eryndil is well thought of for Rangers and Minz Elandil leading in the votes for Scouts. <br>
<br>
And the Peacekeepers? Saffryn refuses to take the name of her blood father, Nobleheart and has taken the name of her new husband, Wardrym, who, himself, dropped the Nobleheart name for the name of his estate, Willowswood. And while they may still argue and throw a bit of mud hear and there, like a willow, they shall bend to one another and their union shall ever be strong. <br>
<br>
The End…of their low level seasons anyway. The mid-level seasons are yet to come.<br>
